# Repo invariants

## Context map

| Need | Read |
|------|------|
| Repo layout, packages | [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) |
| Quick setup | [`README.md`](../../README.md) |
| Compose / layout / troubleshooting | [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) |
| Commands (tables) | [`docs/CHEATSHEET.md`](../../docs/CHEATSHEET.md) |
| Area you edit | Nested `AGENTS.md` under that `apps/` or `packages/` path |
| TypeScript / React deltas | [`typescript.mdc`](typescript.mdc) when editing `.ts` / `.tsx` |
| Multi-phase work | [initiative-workflow](../skills/initiative-workflow/SKILL.md) |

## Quality gate

Before claiming work is done or opening a PR: `bun run overall` (unless the approved plan lists a narrower gate).

## Secrets and config

- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or API keys.
- Read required env vars at use site; throw if missing (do not assume defaults for secrets).

## Initiative work

Phased features: **planning-workflow** → **builder-workflow** (code only) → **documentation-sync** (plan doc list) → **git-pr-workflow**. See [initiative-workflow](../skills/initiative-workflow/SKILL.md).

## Subagents

Spawn policy lives in [builder-workflow](../skills/builder-workflow/SKILL.md) and [orchestration.md](../skills/builder-workflow/orchestration.md) — not in rules.
